text = "Good morning, agent! Are you ready for another day of protecting the sanctity of the timeline?

Since it’s your first day at the Management Agency for Spacetime Kernels - M.A.S.K., as we like to call it - I’m here to train you. But after that, you’re on your own, kapeesh?.

Your job is to review the A.N.C.H.O.R. letters. That’s Authorized Narrative for Chronological Home Orientation and Retention—letters sent from a future decade to a past decade. The big brains in research found that our field agents, after jet-setting all throughout history, needed to “maintain emotional ties” to their time of origin so that their brains didn’t turn all soupy. 

However, you must [b]remove any information that could break the timeline[/b] by censoring it with black ink. Each day, you will be provided with guidelines for what has to be removed. 

When you're done, press the SEND button.
"
